Creat .txt file in YOLO format for every image ✍¶

In [11]:
# Set the path to the directory containing the images
image_dir = "/kaggle/input/vinbigdata-512-image-dataset/vinbigdata/train"

# Set the path to the output directory for the text files
output_dir = "/kaggle/working/Yolo_Training_data/AllLabels"

# Group the dataframe by image_id
grouped = df.groupby("image_id")


# Iterate over the image groups and create a text file for each image
for image_id, group in grouped:
    # Get the path to the image file
    image_path = os.path.join(image_dir, f"{image_id}.png")  # Replace ".png" with the actual image file extension

    # Get the dimensions of the image
    image_width, image_height = group.iloc[0]["width"], group.iloc[0]["height"]

    # Check if the group contains any bounding boxes with class_id == 8
    empty_file = False
    if (group["class_id"] == 8).any():
        empty_file = True

    # Create a list to hold the YOLO-formatted bounding boxes
    boxes = []

    # Iterate over the rows in the group and create a YOLO-formatted bounding box for each row
    for index, row in group.iterrows():
        class_id = row["class_id"]
        if class_id == 8:
            continue  # Skip this bounding box if the class_id is 14

        x_min = row["x_min"]
        y_min = row["y_min"]
        x_max = row["x_max"]
        y_max = row["y_max"]

        # Convert the bounding box coordinates to YOLO format
        x_center = (x_min + x_max) / 2 / image_width
        y_center = (y_min + y_max) / 2 / image_height
        box_width = (x_max - x_min) / image_width
        box_height = (y_max - y_min) / image_height

        # Append the YOLO-formatted bounding box to the list
        boxes.append(f"{class_id} {x_center:.6f} {y_center:.6f} {box_width:.6f} {box_height:.6f}")

    # If the group contains any bounding boxes with class_id == 14, create an empty text file
    if empty_file:
        output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, f"{image_id}.txt")
        open(output_path, "w").close()
        continue

    # Write the YOLO-formatted bounding boxes to a text file
    output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, f"{image_id}.txt")
    with open(output_path, "w") as output_file:
        output_file.write("\n".join(boxes))

In [13]:
# Set the image ID
image_id = '0c5ef740a9befbf439439f0b8e652a0c'

# Load the image
image = cv2.imread('/kaggle/input/vinbigdata-512-image-dataset/vinbigdata/train/0c5ef740a9befbf439439f0b8e652a0c.png')

# Get the image dimensions
image_height, image_width = image.shape[:2]

# Load the bounding box coordinates from a text file
with open('/kaggle/working/Yolo_Training_data/AllLabels/0c5ef740a9befbf439439f0b8e652a0c.txt', 'r') as f:
    bboxes = []
    for line in f:
        cls, x_center, y_center, width, height = map(float, line.split())
        x_min = int((x_center - width / 2) * image_width)
        y_min = int((y_center - height / 2) * image_height)
        x_max = int((x_center + width / 2) * image_width)
        y_max = int((y_center + height / 2) * image_height)
        bboxes.append((x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max))

# Convert the image from BGR to RGB format
image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

# Set the bounding box color (RGB format)
bbox_color = (255, 0, 0)

# Set the bounding box thickness
bbox_thickness = 2

# Draw the bounding boxes on the image
for bbox in bboxes:
    cv2.rectangle(image, (bbox[0], bbox[1]), (bbox[2], bbox[3]), bbox_color, bbox_thickness)

# Display the image with the bounding boxes using matplotlib
plt.imshow(image)
plt.show()

In [15]:
def preproccess_data(df, labels_path, images_path):
    for img_id in tqdm(df.image_id.unique()):
        shutil.copy(os.path.join('/kaggle/working/Yolo_Training_data/AllLabels', f"{img_id}"+'.txt'), labels_path)
        shutil.copy(os.path.join(f'/kaggle/input/vinbigdata-512-image-dataset/vinbigdata/train', f"{img_id}.png"), images_path)

    train =  '/kaggle/working/Yolo_Training_data/images/train',
    val   =  '/kaggle/working/Yolo_Training_data/images/val',
    nc    = 8,
    names = classes
